headline: Private Credit’s Biggest BDCs Grappling With Investor Exodus
summary: The biggest lenders were hit with a spike in requests from investors to withdraw money from their large non-traded business development companies in the three months through December.

headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Blackstone (BX) After Strong Multi Year Share Price Gains?
summary: If you are looking at Blackstone and wondering whether the current share price still makes sense, you are not alone. Many investors are asking the same question. The stock recently closed at US$155.30, with returns of 0.8% over 7 days, a 0.5% decline over 30 days, a 2.2% decline year to date, an 8.0% decline over 1 year, and very large gains over 3 and 5 years at 99.9% and 190.7% respectively.
